Key Match Events: Liam Livingstone smashed five sixes in a pulsating 87
Matt Short took five wickets in 2.5 overs
Phil Salt hit three successive sixes
Pre-Game Insights: England win the toss and bowl
Travis Head’s verdict: 'I thought 193 was a good score and we were right in the game.'
Phil Salt: 'We know how good they are at the top of the order so we’ll have to go back to our plans.'
Liam Livingstone: 'It’s not easy coming in at No6 and No7. I’m not complain, I’m not gonna cry about it. But moving up the order is nice, it gives me more responsbility and more time to bat.'
Post-Match Reflections: Liam Livingstone: 'I did say towards the end of The Hundred that I felt like I was getting my body back to normal, which hasn’t been the case for a while. The last couple of years have taught me a few life lessons. I’m enjoying my cricket and playing with a smile on my face.'
Jacob Bethell: 'He’s a real talent. Jacob’s started really well in this series and hopefully he takes that form to Old Trafford.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: Conditions changed, but we knew that at the toss.
It’s not easy coming in at No6 and No7.
